HEADWORD: Prosper
<hw>Pros"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Prospered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Prospering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>prosp⟦eacute⟧rer</ets> v. i., or L. <ets>prosperare</ets>, v. i.,
or L. <ets>prosperare</ets>, v. t., fr. <ets>prosper or prosperus</ets>.
See <er>Prosperous</er>.]</ety> <def>To favor; to render
successful.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Prosper</xex> thou our handiwork.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bk. of Common Prayer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All things concur to<qex>prosper</qex> our design.</q>
