==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prosper
<hw>Pros"per</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To be successful;
to succeed; to be fortunate or prosperous; to thrive; to make
gain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They, in their earthly Canaan placed,⟦br⟧
Long time shall dwell and <qex>prosper</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To grow; to increase.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Black cherry trees <qex>prosper</qex> even to considerable
timber.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prosperity</ent>⟦br⟧
